terest to students of sociology, anthropology, and religion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAboriginal AustraliansxEthnic identity. 0aAboriginal AustraliansxReligion. 0aMythology, Aboriginal Australian. 4aHistory. 4aReligion. 4aSocial Science: Anthropology. 7aRELIGION / Ethnic & Tribal.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920678640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889206786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889206786/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles